      • MastersStudent

        public MastersStudent(java.lang.String theFirstName,
                      java.lang.String theLastName,
                      java.lang.String theID,
                      int theCreditHours,
                      double theGPA,
                      MastersStatus theStatus,
                      Gender theGender,
                      java.util.Date theBirth,
                      java.util.Date theDate)
        Parameterized constructor - constructors a MastersStudent object.
        Parameters:
        theFirstName - is a string representing the first name of a student, != null
        theLastName - is a string representing the last name of a student, != null
        theID - is a string of 9 characters representing student ID
        theCreditHours - is an integer number >=0 representing number of credit hours taken by a student
        theGPA - is a double number representing GPA, a GPA must be >= 0 and <= 4.0
        theStatus - is a string representing student status, != null
        theGender - is a character representing student gender, != null
        theBirth - is a date representing student birth date; a student cannot be younger than 10 years old
        theDate - is date the student started in the program
        Post Condition:
        MastersStudent object constructed; if invalid parameters passed, student is in an invalid state.
